text.text: I live no where near BCC but will make the drive when I‚Äôm craving their Toe Beans! Truly the best coffee at an amazing price. Love the atmosphere inside. So chic and cool. Very chill. Give this place a try you won‚Äôt be disappointed.

Great coffee!!!! Easily 5 stars for this coffee cafe !! Love the location! Beautiful interior setting, big and spacious, you can chill, relax or even study here. Decorated nicely as well. The coffee came out hot and delicious, I like that they already have specialty coffee flavor mixes on the menu, only drawback on the coffee is I wish they‚Äôd use locally roasted coffee beans. Best of luck, hope you are open here for years to come! üíû Will definitely be back to try out the food and of course to get more coffee. Yum üòã

cafes.name: Cat's Coffee & Creamery
cafes.address: 107 S Washington St, DeRidder, LA 70634, USA

text.text:
Got a small Green Tea and a double shot with light 1/2 & 1/2.
Customer service was good. I love traditional coffees and really appreciated that the barista asked questions about my order to make sure she knew what i wanted. Espresso is lighter than i expected but still good! Green tea is sweet by itself but not over powering. Prices are great here, very reasonable. Will go here again!

I had been ordering from door dash and I just wasn't getting the drink I had in mind. I was looking for somethin on the lines of that vanilla bean drink that's at Starbucks but maybe with a twist if it tastes good. I told the berista at Cats what I needed and she got to work. Yall it was better than the 1 at Starbucks. She wrote what I got on my cup ( thank you!!) I snapped a pic of it ( will post later). For my non coffee drinkers this is the place üëåüèæ and it's quiet n there to do your work.

Service was fast. The barista was friendly and offered multiple different options for my coffee including different milks and add ins. Very knowledgeable. It‚Äôs so cozy and the music is always a nice touch.

cafes.name: BEARCAT CAFE UPTOWN
cafes.address: 2521 Jena St, New Orleans, LA 70115, USA

text.text: As advertised. Really good brunch food with an interesting enough menu. Service was extremely friendly and attentive despite it being a very busy weekend brunch. This place can be a bit loud and overwhelming if you don‚Äôt like bustling restaurants with open kitchens. Only knock would be the price. Although I was pleased overall, I was not expecting a 3-digit bill. (2 entrees, 2 juices, one order of pancakes and an Irish coffee)

Wonderful food 100% worth the wait. The textures, flavor, and visual were all perfect. Ask wait staff for reccomendations because they are wonderful. Staff was super friendly. Love you can view the open kitchen. Also, the check-in process using Yelp is super easy and convenient. I will be frequenting Bearcat anytime I come back to visit. Stay AHHHMAZING Bearcat.

If you‚Äôre in NOLA do not miss this spot ü§§ came in for brunch and this place DID NOT disappoint!! They have a variety of lattes- lavender honey was my favorite. Had the crab scramble and everything on the plate was incredible. They were generous with the crab and the potatoes were seasoned perfectly. Service was excellent and attentive. Parking was easy. They have free parking on the side of the restaurant if you can‚Äôt find street parking.

cafes.name: BEARCAT CBD
cafes.address: 845 Carondelet St, New Orleans, LA 70130, USA

text.text:
The food was good here. The atmosphere was good here. The service left much to be desired.
I got the yogurt with granola and fresh fruit. I also got a lemon gluten-free muffin. Hubby got the breakfast club. We both got the fresh squeezed orange juice.
One waiter took our order, and then he disappeared. When we waved down another waiter she she said that she was our waiter. Huh!?  Since she didn't check on us we had no idea that she was our waiter.

Great service. Better food. My friends and I visited on a work trip and the breakfast was exactly what we needed after a night out in the french quarter. The scallops and grits were the best grits i have ever had. And perfectly cooked scallops.
I also forgot my receipt at the restaurant and they were so helpful and prompt in sending me a copy within 20 minutes of requesting it.
Cant wait to visit again!

We got the couyon daddy, breakfast club sandwich and a side of (very tasty &) crispy potatoes, grits (super creamy) & blueberry pancakes. Everything was delicious!! When we arrived there was a large crowd of people outside waiting for tables - in fact, there were 23 parties in front of us but we only waited 35 minutes for a seat. We sat at the bar and got custom drinks from the awesome bartenders üòä All the staff were pleasant. We absolutely loved it and will surely return the next time we‚Äôre in NOLA. So glad we stopped here!

Pass Christian.name: Cat Island Coffeehouse
Pass Christian.address: 300 E Scenic Dr, Pass Christian, MS 39571, USA

text.text: Really cool coffee shop/book store. If you're looking for a cozy place to grab some coffee and read a book, then look no further. This place is somewhat quiet and very cozy. I could hang out here all day drinking coffee while reading a book.

There are a few great coffee shops along the Gulf Coast of Mississippi and Cat Island Coffee Shop ranks near the top. The coffee and Lattes are great but the views of the MS sound are what sets it apart. The seating is limited but we have always had a place to sit and an excellent experience. It's a great place to stop off when driving the beach on a pretty day.

A very special little Coffee and Book haven situated across the Beach Hwy from the Gulf and the Pass Christian Harbor.  It is located right on the corner.
This place is so warm and comfortable. While you enjoy their wonderful coffee brews accompanied  by selections of b'fast sandwiches or cobbler or muffins, etc. I was in town visiting a great couple that live just down the elevated road. They walk down to the coffeehouse just about every day. That is informative about the coffee consistency, because my buddy, Artie is very frugal...

cafes.name: Cat Haven
cafes.address: 11130 N Harrells Ferry Rd, Baton Rouge, LA 70816, USA

text.text: We adopted Barley (Beta, Betus) from Cat Haven, and he‚Äôs been the most adorable, goofy little furball! We instantly fell in love with him. The adoption process was seamless, and the staff at Cat Haven were incredibly helpful and kind. Highly recommend this wonderful place for anyone looking to adopt!
Love my baby! The place was clean other cats in their care looked happy and healthy. Will probably go back and adopt another kitten!

We adopted Winston and Willow (Simone) from Cat Haven a few weeks ago. Our kitties are so spoiled and love their new life at the furever home. Cat Haven was great! No pressure, and so patient answering all of our questions and let us come back and spend time before making our decision. It is different from other places with rooms and toys for the kitties and everyone there loves cats! I highly recommend Cat Haven to anyone looking to adopt.

Los Angeles.name: CatCafe Lounge | Cats + Kittens + Catio
Los Angeles.address: 1736 S Sepulveda Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90025, USA

text.text: This place is very small, but it is very clean, well maintained, and comforting not only for the guests, but most importantly, for the cats. The reservation fee is pricey, however this business is a non profit that focuses on rehabilitating rescued cats, and it has a great mission and appears to be working very hard and ethically to give these cats a chance at adoption. The cats have plenty of space to roam around and sit, sleep, and play anywhere they like. The cats also have easy access to food, water, and litter boxes. I highly recommend this location for anyone who loves cats. You‚Äôll have a great time here and the time will fly by too fast. It is also a great business to support! I‚Äôll definitely be coming back soon ;)

My son loves this place and all the kitties! Our cat is mature and doesn‚Äôt play with him, so he was absolutely thrilled when little kittens started playing with him and following him. I really like that they have a nice outdoor catio where cats enjoy sunshine and chill.
Friendly staff and such a huge amount of space for the kitties. Cats looked very well taken care of and space was clean as well. I loved the mixed outdoor/indoor space.
